    <div class="gf__post-content gf__post-content--align-left">
                      <div class="gf__post-content-date">
          <span class="lal-f1 lal-f1--serious">Sep 27, 2019</span>
        </div>
              
      
      <div class="gf__post-content-title gf__post-content-title--medium gf__post-content-title--dark">
        <h1 class="lal-f2">
          <a href="https://lawliberty.org/first-virtue-prudence-burke-lincoln-greg-weiner-old-whigs-review/">The First Virtue of Old Whigs: Prudence in Burke and Lincoln</a>
        <h1>
      </div>

                        <div class="gf__post-content-authors gf__post-content-authors--dark">
      
    
    <span class="gf__post-content-authors-author lal-f2 lal-f2--small-caps lal-f2--semibold"><a href="https://lawliberty.org/author/daniel-e-ritchie/">Daniel E. Ritchie</a></span>
    </div>
        
                <div class="gf__post-content-summary gf__post-content-summary--dark">
          <p class="lal-f2">Weiner’s <em>Old Whigs</em> offers a persuasive account of how Burke and Lincoln negotiate the tensions between principle and prudence.</p>
        </div>
              
    </div>

  </div>

</article>
